House prices soared in Hengqin, South China's Guangdong Province, after a plan to develop the town into an international resort island was approved by State Council on April 1. New house prices have exceeded 42,000 yuan ($6,242) per square meter, approaching those of Shenzhen. Hengqin is the third island in China that has been designated for development into an international tourism island. According to the plan, Hengqin's construction will coordinate with Macao's tourism development. Photo: IC Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun